{
  "video_id": "5foou7mIA0w",
  "title": "Why theater is essential to democracy | Oskar Eustis",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13595.0,
      "end_time": 17268.0,
      "text": "Theater matters because democracy matters."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17653.0,
      "end_time": 21572.0,
      "text": "Theater is the essential art form of democracy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 21596.0,
      "end_time": 25864.0,
      "text": "and we know this because they were born in the same city."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 26245.0,
      "end_time": 28332.0,
      "text": "In the late 6th century BC,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 28356.0,
      "end_time": 30215.0,
      "text": "the idea of Western democracy was born."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 30239.0,
      "end_time": 31748.0,
      "text": "It was, of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31772.0,
      "end_time": 34234.0,
      "text": "a very partial and flawed democracy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 34258.0,
      "end_time": 39213.0,
      "text": "but the idea that power should stem from the consent of the governed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 39237.0,
      "end_time": 42665.0,
      "text": "that power should flow from below to above,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 42689.0,
      "end_time": 44300.0,
      "text": "not the other way around,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 44324.0,
      "end_time": 45884.0,
      "text": "was born in that decade."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 45908.0,
      "end_time": 51920.0,
      "text": "And in that same decade, somebody -- legend has it, somebody named Thespis --"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 51116.0,
      "end_time": 53260.0,
      "text": "invented the idea of dialogue."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 53284.0,
      "end_time": 55190.0,
      "text": "What does that mean, to invent dialogue?"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 55214.0,
      "end_time": 57839.0,
      "text": "Well, we know that the Festival of Dionysus gathered"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 57864.0,
      "end_time": 59397.0,
      "text": "the entire citizenry of Athens"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 59422.0,
      "end_time": 61129.0,
      "text": "on the side of the Acropolis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 61154.0,
      "end_time": 64453.0,
      "text": "and they would listen to music, they would watch dancing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 64477.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67922.0,
      "text": "and they would have stories told as part of the Festival of Dionysus."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 68314.0,
      "end_time": 71800.0,
      "text": "And storytelling is much like what's happening right now:"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 71330.0,
      "end_time": 72588.0,
      "text": "I'm standing up here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 72612.0,
      "end_time": 74633.0,
      "text": "the unitary authority,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 74657.0,
      "end_time": 76215.0,
      "text": "and I am talking to you."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 76239.0,
      "end_time": 79629.0,
      "text": "And you are sitting back, and you are receiving what I have to say."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 79653.0,
      "end_time": 83870.0,
      "text": "And you may disagree with it, you may think I'm an insufferable fool,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 83111.0,
      "end_time": 84719.0,
      "text": "you may be bored to death,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 84743.0,
      "end_time": 87878.0,
      "text": "but that dialogue is mostly taking place inside your own head."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 88577.0,
      "end_time": 92676.0,
      "text": "But what happens if, instead of me talking to you --"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 92701.0,
      "end_time": 94681.0,
      "text": "and Thespis thought of this --"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 94705.0,
      "end_time": 97456.0,
      "text": "I just shift 90 degrees to the left,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 97480.0,
      "end_time": 100150.0,
      "text": "and I talk to another person onstage with me?"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 101900.0,
      "end_time": 103326.0,
      "text": "Everything changes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 103350.0,
      "end_time": 107274.0,
      "text": "because at that moment, I'm not the possessor of truth;"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 107299.0,
      "end_time": 109549.0,
      "text": "I'm a guy with an opinion."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 110260.0,
      "end_time": 111856.0,
      "text": "And I'm talking to somebody else."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 111880.0,
      "end_time": 113300.0,
      "text": "And you know what?"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 113550.0,
      "end_time": 115508.0,
      "text": "That other person has an opinion too,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 115532.0,
      "end_time": 118936.0,
      "text": "and it's drama, remember, conflict -- they disagree with me."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 119522.0,
      "end_time": 122467.0,
      "text": "There's a conflict between two points of view."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 122491.0,
      "end_time": 128787.0,
      "text": "And the thesis of that is that the truth can only emerge"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 128811.0,
      "end_time": 131830.0,
      "text": "in the conflict of different points of view."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 131107.0,
      "end_time": 133841.0,
      "text": "It's not the possession of any one person."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 133865.0,
      "end_time": 137675.0,
      "text": "And if you believe in democracy, you have to believe that."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 138136.0,
      "end_time": 140576.0,
      "text": "If you don't believe that, you're an autocrat"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 140600.0,
      "end_time": 142266.0,
      "text": "who is putting up with democracy."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 142778.0,
      "end_time": 145298.0,
      "text": "But that's the basic thesis of democracy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 145322.0,
      "end_time": 148451.0,
      "text": "that the conflict of different points of views leads to the truth."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 148475.0,
      "end_time": 150434.0,
      "text": "What's the other thing that's happening?"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 150458.0,
      "end_time": 153101.0,
      "text": "I'm not asking you to sit back and listen to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 153125.0,
      "end_time": 155376.0,
      "text": "I'm asking you to lean forward"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 155400.0,
      "end_time": 158482.0,
      "text": "and imagine my point of view --"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 158506.0,
      "end_time": 162105.0,
      "text": "what this looks like and feels like to me as a character."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 162129.0,
      "end_time": 165600.0,
      "text": "And then I'm asking you to switch your mind"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 165850.0,
      "end_time": 168437.0,
      "text": "and imagine what it feels like to the other person talking."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 169200.0,
      "end_time": 171940.0,
      "text": "I'm asking you to exercise empathy."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 172671.0,
      "end_time": 176515.0,
      "text": "And the idea that truth comes from the collision of different ideas"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 176539.0,
      "end_time": 179432.0,
      "text": "and the emotional muscle of empathy"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 179456.0,
      "end_time": 183300.0,
      "text": "are the necessary tools for democratic citizenship."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 183722.0,
      "end_time": 185705.0,
      "text": "What else happens?"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 185729.0,
      "end_time": 187976.0,
      "text": "The third thing really is you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 188000.0,
      "end_time": 190802.0,
      "text": "is the community itself, is the audience."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 191322.0,
      "end_time": 195311.0,
      "text": "And you know from personal experience that when you go to the movies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 195335.0,
      "end_time": 198583.0,
      "text": "you walk into a movie theater, and if it's empty, you're delighted,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 198607.0,
      "end_time": 201265.0,
      "text": "because nothing's going to be between you and the movie."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 201289.0,
      "end_time": 204500.0,
      "text": "You can spread out, put your legs over the top of the stadium seats,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 204525.0,
      "end_time": 206233.0,
      "text": "eat your popcorn and just enjoy it."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 206257.0,
      "end_time": 208159.0,
      "text": "But if you walk into a live theater"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 208183.0,
      "end_time": 210626.0,
      "text": "and you see that the theater is half full,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 210650.0,
      "end_time": 211942.0,
      "text": "your heart sinks."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 212420.0,
      "end_time": 214476.0,
      "text": "You're disappointed immediately,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 214501.0,
      "end_time": 216500.0,
      "text": "because whether you knew it or not,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 216524.0,
      "end_time": 218420.0,
      "text": "you were coming to that theater"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 218444.0,
      "end_time": 220298.0,
      "text": "to be part of an audience."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 220323.0,
      "end_time": 223232.0,
      "text": "You were coming to have the collective experience"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 223256.0,
      "end_time": 226827.0,
      "text": "of laughing together, crying together, holding your breath together"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 226851.0,
      "end_time": 228576.0,
      "text": "to see what's going to happen next."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 228600.0,
      "end_time": 233830.0,
      "text": "You may have walked into that theater as an individual consumer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 233107.0,
      "end_time": 235734.0,
      "text": "but if the theater does its job,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 235758.0,
      "end_time": 239441.0,
      "text": "you've walked out with a sense of yourself as part of a whole,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 239465.0,
      "end_time": 240881.0,
      "text": "as part of a community."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 241643.0,
      "end_time": 245654.0,
      "text": "That's built into the DNA of my art form."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 246678.0,
      "end_time": 251220.0,
      "text": "Twenty-five hundred years later, Joe Papp decided"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 251244.0,
      "end_time": 255203.0,
      "text": "that the culture should belong to everybody in the United States of America,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 255227.0,
      "end_time": 259230.0,
      "text": "and that it was his job to try to deliver on that promise."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 259470.00000000003,
      "end_time": 261925.00000000003,
      "text": "He created Free Shakespeare in the Park."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 261949.0,
      "end_time": 265450.0,
      "text": "And Free Shakespeare in the Park is based on a very simple idea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 265690.0,
      "end_time": 269639.0,
      "text": "the idea that the best theater, the best art that we can produce,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 269663.0,
      "end_time": 272473.0,
      "text": "should go to everybody and belong to everybody,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 272497.0,
      "end_time": 274238.0,
      "text": "and to this day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 274262.0,
      "end_time": 276651.0,
      "text": "every summer night in Central Park,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 276675.0,
      "end_time": 279520.0,
      "text": "2,000 people are lining up"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 279760.0,
      "end_time": 282700.0,
      "text": "to see the best theater we can provide for free."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 282724.0,
      "end_time": 285566.0,
      "text": "It's not a commercial transaction."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 285590.0,
      "end_time": 290610.0,
      "text": "In 1967, 13 years after he figured that out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 290850.0,
      "end_time": 291732.0,
      "text": "he figured out something else,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 291756.0,
      "end_time": 295313.0,
      "text": "which is that the democratic circle was not complete"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 295337.0,
      "end_time": 298563.0,
      "text": "by just giving the people the classics."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 298588.0,
      "end_time": 302125.0,
      "text": "We had to actually let the people create their own classics"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 302149.0,
      "end_time": 303964.0,
      "text": "and take the stage."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 303988.0,
      "end_time": 306450.0,
      "text": "And so in 1967,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 306690.0,
      "end_time": 309128.0,
      "text": "Joe opened the Public Theater downtown on Astor Place,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 309152.0,
      "end_time": 313370.0,
      "text": "and the first show he ever produced was the world premiere of \"Hair.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 313394.0,
      "end_time": 316182.0,
      "text": "That's the first thing he ever did that wasn't Shakespeare."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 316206.0,
      "end_time": 319517.0,
      "text": "Clive Barnes in The Times said that it was as if Mr. Papp took a broom"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 319541.0,
      "end_time": 322803.0,
      "text": "and swept up all the refuse from the East Village streets"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 322827.0,
      "end_time": 325166.0,
      "text": "onto the stage at the Public."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 325190.0,
      "end_time": 326194.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 326218.0,
      "end_time": 327995.0,
      "text": "He didn't mean it complementarily,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 328190.0,
      "end_time": 331550.0,
      "text": "but Joe put it up in the lobby, he was so proud of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 331574.0,
      "end_time": 333500.0,
      "text": "(Laughter) (Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 333740.0,
      "end_time": 337494.0,
      "text": "And what the Public Theater did over the next years with amazing shows like"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 337518.0,
      "end_time": 341420.0,
      "text": "\"For Colored Girls Who Have Considered Suicide / When the Rainbow Is Enuf,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 341660.0,
      "end_time": 343833.0,
      "text": "\"A Chorus Line,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 343858.0,
      "end_time": 347890.0,
      "text": "and -- here's the most extraordinary example I can think of:"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 347914.0,
      "end_time": 353168.0,
      "text": "Larry Kramer's savage cry of rage about the AIDS crisis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 353192.0,
      "end_time": 354514.0,
      "text": "\"The Normal Heart.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 354880.0,
      "end_time": 358929.0,
      "text": "Because when Joe produced that play in 1985,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 358953.0,
      "end_time": 361994.0,
      "text": "there was more information about AIDS"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 362190.0,
      "end_time": 365210.0,
      "text": "in Frank Rich's review in the New York Times"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 365234.0,
      "end_time": 368659.0,
      "text": "than the New York Times had published in the previous four years."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 368684.0,
      "end_time": 373840.0,
      "text": "Larry was actually changing the dialogue about AIDS"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 373108.0,
      "end_time": 374495.0,
      "text": "through writing this play,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 374519.0,
      "end_time": 375922.0,
      "text": "and Joe was by producing it."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 375946.0,
      "end_time": 380391.0,
      "text": "I was blessed to commission and work on Tony Kushner's \"Angels in America,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 380415.0,
      "end_time": 384630.0,
      "text": "and when doing that play and along with \"Normal Heart,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 384870.0,
      "end_time": 387435.0,
      "text": "we could see that the culture was actually shifting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 387459.0,
      "end_time": 389488.0,
      "text": "and it wasn't caused by the theater,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 389512.0,
      "end_time": 391967.0,
      "text": "but the theater was doing its part"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 391991.0,
      "end_time": 396265.0,
      "text": "to change what it meant to be gay in the United States."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 396290.0,
      "end_time": 398130.0,
      "text": "And I'm incredibly proud of that."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 398605.0,
      "end_time": 400498.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 400522.0,
      "end_time": 405318.0,
      "text": "When I took over Joe's old job at the Public in 2005,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 405342.0,
      "end_time": 409770.0,
      "text": "I realized one of the problems we had was a victim of our own success,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 409101.0,
      "end_time": 414126.0,
      "text": "which is: Shakespeare in the Park had been founded as a program for access,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 414150.0,
      "end_time": 417700.0,
      "text": "and it was now the hardest ticket to get in New York City."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 417725.0,
      "end_time": 421640.0,
      "text": "People slept out for two nights to get those tickets."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 421664.0,
      "end_time": 422820.0,
      "text": "What was that doing?"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 422845.0,
      "end_time": 425438.0,
      "text": "That was eliminating 98 percent of the population"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 425462.0,
      "end_time": 427291.0,
      "text": "from even considering going to it."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 427315.0,
      "end_time": 429545.0,
      "text": "So we refounded the mobile unit"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 429569.0,
      "end_time": 432648.0,
      "text": "and took Shakespeare to prisons, to homeless shelters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 432672.0,
      "end_time": 435160.0,
      "text": "to community centers in all five boroughs"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 435184.0,
      "end_time": 437875.0,
      "text": "and even in New Jersey and Westchester County."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 437899.0,
      "end_time": 442103.0,
      "text": "And that program proved something to us that we knew intuitively:"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 442127.0,
      "end_time": 446867.0,
      "text": "people's need for theater is as powerful as their desire for food"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 446891.0,
      "end_time": 448135.0,
      "text": "or for drink."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 448560.0,
      "end_time": 451403.0,
      "text": "It's been an extraordinary success, and we've continued it."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 451427.0,
      "end_time": 455116.0,
      "text": "And then there was yet another barrier that we realized we weren't crossing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 455140.0,
      "end_time": 457404.0,
      "text": "which is a barrier of participation."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 457428.0,
      "end_time": 458726.0,
      "text": "And the idea, we said, is:"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 458750.0,
      "end_time": 463269.0,
      "text": "How can we turn theater from being a commodity, an object,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 463293.0,
      "end_time": 465535.0,
      "text": "back into what it really is --"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 465559.0,
      "end_time": 468980.0,
      "text": "a set of relationships among people?"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 468122.0,
      "end_time": 471140.0,
      "text": "And under the guidance of the amazing Lear deBessonet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 471380.0,
      "end_time": 472916.0,
      "text": "we started the Public Works program,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 472940.0,
      "end_time": 474832.0,
      "text": "which now every summer produces"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 474856.0,
      "end_time": 477698.0,
      "text": "these immense Shakespearean musical pageants,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 477722.0,
      "end_time": 480486.0,
      "text": "where Tony Award-winning actors and musicians"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 480510.0,
      "end_time": 484356.0,
      "text": "are side by side with nannies and domestic workers"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 484380.0,
      "end_time": 488254.0,
      "text": "and military veterans and recently incarcerated prisoners,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 488278.0,
      "end_time": 489873.0,
      "text": "amateurs and professionals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 489897.0,
      "end_time": 492331.0,
      "text": "performing together on the same stage."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 492355.0,
      "end_time": 494352.0,
      "text": "And it's not just a great social program,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 494376.0,
      "end_time": 496486.0,
      "text": "it's the best art that we do."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 496825.0,
      "end_time": 500954.0,
      "text": "And the thesis of it is that artistry is not something"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 500978.0,
      "end_time": 503690.0,
      "text": "that is the possession of a few."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 503930.0,
      "end_time": 506461.0,
      "text": "Artistry is inherent in being a human being."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 506485.0,
      "end_time": 510840.0,
      "text": "Some of us just get to spend a lot more of our lives practicing it."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 511252.0,
      "end_time": 512403.0,
      "text": "And then occasionally --"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 512427.0,
      "end_time": 514325.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 514349.00000000006,
      "end_time": 516452.00000000006,
      "text": "you get a miracle like \"Hamilton,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 516476.0,
      "end_time": 522596.0,
      "text": "Lin-Manuel's extraordinary retelling of the foundational story of this country"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 522620.0,
      "end_time": 527426.0,
      "text": "through the eyes of the only Founding Father who was a bastard immigrant orphan"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 527450.0,
      "end_time": 529600.0,
      "text": "from the West Indies."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 529300.0,
      "end_time": 530768.0,
      "text": "And what Lin was doing"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 530792.0,
      "end_time": 533255.0,
      "text": "is exactly what Shakespeare was doing."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 533645.0,
      "end_time": 537853.0,
      "text": "He was taking the voice of the people, the language of the people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 537878.0,
      "end_time": 540135.0,
      "text": "elevating it into verse,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 540159.0,
      "end_time": 541723.0,
      "text": "and by doing so,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 541747.0,
      "end_time": 543548.0,
      "text": "ennobling the language"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 543572.0,
      "end_time": 546909.0,
      "text": "and ennobling the people who spoke the language."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 546933.0,
      "end_time": 551717.0,
      "text": "And by casting that show entirely with a cast of black and brown people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 551741.0,
      "end_time": 554204.0,
      "text": "what Lin was saying to us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 554228.0,
      "end_time": 556832.0,
      "text": "he was reviving in us"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 556856.0,
      "end_time": 560451.0,
      "text": "our greatest aspirations for the United States,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 560475.0,
      "end_time": 562826.0,
      "text": "our better angels of America,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 562850.0,
      "end_time": 565255.0,
      "text": "our sense of what this country could be,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 565279.0,
      "end_time": 569418.0,
      "text": "the inclusion that was at the heart of the American Dream."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 569442.0,
      "end_time": 573668.0,
      "text": "And it unleashed a wave of patriotism in me"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 573692.0,
      "end_time": 575140.0,
      "text": "and in our audience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 575380.0,
      "end_time": 578865.0,
      "text": "the appetite for which is proving to be insatiable."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 580132.0,
      "end_time": 583224.0,
      "text": "But there was another side to that, and it's where I want to end,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 583249.0,
      "end_time": 585420.0,
      "text": "and it's the last story I want to talk about."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 585444.0,
      "end_time": 588216.0,
      "text": "Some of you may have heard that Vice President-elect Pence"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 588240.0,
      "end_time": 590962.0,
      "text": "came to see \"Hamilton\" in New York."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 590986.0,
      "end_time": 595400.0,
      "text": "And when he came in, some of my fellow New Yorkers booed him."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 595640.0,
      "end_time": 596899.0,
      "text": "And beautifully, he said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 596923.0,
      "end_time": 598973.0,
      "text": "\"That's what freedom sounds like.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 599799.0,
      "end_time": 601170.0,
      "text": "And at the end of the show,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 601195.0,
      "end_time": 604388.0,
      "text": "we read what I feel was a very respectful statement from the stage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 604412.0,
      "end_time": 607267.0,
      "text": "and Vice President-elect Pence listened to it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 607790.0,
      "end_time": 611694.0,
      "text": "but it sparked a certain amount of outrage, a tweetstorm,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 611719.0,
      "end_time": 615293.0,
      "text": "and also an internet boycott of \"Hamilton\""
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 615317.0,
      "end_time": 619453.0,
      "text": "from outraged people who had felt we had treated him with disrespect."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 620142.0,
      "end_time": 624670.0,
      "text": "I looked at that boycott and I said, we're getting something wrong here."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 624910.0,
      "end_time": 627410.0,
      "text": "All of these people who have signed this boycott petition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 627434.0,
      "end_time": 629699.0,
      "text": "they were never going to see \"Hamilton\" anyway."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 630520.0,
      "end_time": 632637.0,
      "text": "It was never going to come to a city near them."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 632661.0,
      "end_time": 635219.0,
      "text": "If it could come, they couldn't afford a ticket,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 635244.0,
      "end_time": 638736.0,
      "text": "and if they could afford a ticket, they didn't have the connections"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 638760.0,
      "end_time": 640161.0,
      "text": "to get that ticket."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 640691.0,
      "end_time": 642546.0,
      "text": "They weren't boycotting us;"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 643660.0,
      "end_time": 645980.0,
      "text": "we had boycotted them."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 646187.0,
      "end_time": 650483.0,
      "text": "And if you look at the red and blue electoral map of the United States,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 650507.0,
      "end_time": 651819.0,
      "text": "and if I were to tell you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 651844.0,
      "end_time": 653899.0,
      "text": "\"Oh, the blue is what designates"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 653923.0,
      "end_time": 656879.0,
      "text": "all of the major nonprofit cultural institutions,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 656903.0,
      "end_time": 658338.0,
      "text": "I'd be telling you the truth."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 658362.0,
      "end_time": 659568.0,
      "text": "You'd believe me."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 659592.0,
      "end_time": 664194.0,
      "text": "We in the culture have done exactly what the economy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 664219.0,
      "end_time": 667849.0,
      "text": "what the educational system, what technology has done,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 667873.0,
      "end_time": 671548.0,
      "text": "which is turn our back on a large part of the country."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 672100.0,
      "end_time": 675110.0,
      "text": "So this idea of inclusion, it has to keep going."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 675134.0,
      "end_time": 678256.0,
      "text": "Next fall, we are sending out on tour"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 678280.0,
      "end_time": 683468.0,
      "text": "a production of Lynn Nottage's brilliant, Pulitzer Prize-winning play \"Sweat.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 683493.0,
      "end_time": 687872.0,
      "text": "Years of research in Redding, Pennsylvania led her to write this play"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 687896.0,
      "end_time": 691121.0,
      "text": "about the deindustrialization of Pennsylvania:"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 691145.0,
      "end_time": 693793.0,
      "text": "what happened when steel left,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 693817.0,
      "end_time": 696770.0,
      "text": "the rage that was unleashed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 696101.0,
      "end_time": 697732.0,
      "text": "the tensions that were unleashed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 697756.0,
      "end_time": 700160.0,
      "text": "the racism that was unleashed"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 700400.0,
      "end_time": 701531.0,
      "text": "by the loss of jobs."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 701949.0,
      "end_time": 704924.0,
      "text": "We're taking that play and we're touring it"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 704948.0,
      "end_time": 707737.0,
      "text": "to rural counties in Pennsylvania,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 707761.0,
      "end_time": 709988.0,
      "text": "Ohio, Michigan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 710130.0,
      "end_time": 712340.0,
      "text": "Minnesota and Wisconsin."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 712364.0,
      "end_time": 716825.0,
      "text": "We're partnering with community organizations there to try and make sure"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 716849.0,
      "end_time": 720775.0,
      "text": "not only that we reach the people that we're trying to reach,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 720799.0,
      "end_time": 723677.0,
      "text": "but that we find ways to listen to them back"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 723701.0,
      "end_time": 727334.0,
      "text": "and say, \"The culture is here for you, too.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 727962.0,
      "end_time": 729115.0,
      "text": "Because --"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 729139.0,
      "end_time": 731567.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 731591.0,
      "end_time": 733737.0,
      "text": "we in the culture industry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 733761.0,
      "end_time": 735860.0,
      "text": "we in the theater,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 735884.0,
      "end_time": 739496.0,
      "text": "have no right to say that we don't know what our job is."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 739520.0,
      "end_time": 741545.0,
      "text": "It's in the DNA of our art form."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 741570.0,
      "end_time": 746229.0,
      "text": "Our job \"... is to hold up, as 'twere, a mirror to nature;"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 746253.0,
      "end_time": 748932.0,
      "text": "to show scorn her image,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 748956.0,
      "end_time": 751989.0,
      "text": "to show virtue her appearance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 752130.0,
      "end_time": 755277.0,
      "text": "and the very age its form and pressure.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 755301.0,
      "end_time": 759670.0,
      "text": "Our job is to try to hold up a vision to America"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 759694.0,
      "end_time": 763757.0,
      "text": "that shows not only who all of us are individually,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 763781.0,
      "end_time": 768880.0,
      "text": "but that welds us back into the commonality that we need to be,"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 768112.0,
      "end_time": 769921.0,
      "text": "the sense of unity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 769946.0,
      "end_time": 771618.0,
      "text": "the sense of whole,"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 771642.0,
      "end_time": 773790.0,
      "text": "the sense of who we are as a country."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 774398.0,
      "end_time": 777125.0,
      "text": "That's what the theater is supposed to do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 777149.0,
      "end_time": 779778.0,
      "text": "and that's what we need to try to do as well as we can."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 779802.0,
      "end_time": 781780.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 781102.0,
      "end_time": 786000.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}